title: Why Take-Two Interactive Stock Leaped 6% Higher Today
description: Rumor of a potential buyout from a big-pocketed strategic investor was inflating the share price of video game company Take-Two Interactive Software (NASDAQ: TTWO) on Thursday.  The hot gossip is that none other than Japanese tech and entertainment giant Sony (NYSE: SONY) is the interested party.  Apparently, the company will make a play to buy Take-Two if Microsoft succeeds in its determination to acquire Take-Two's fellow video game maker Activision Blizzard.
